<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
FLORIDA; 
</P>
<P>
WINTER CHILL BRINGS RECORD READINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cold air that blanketed much of the eastern half of the nation brought record 
low temperatures to Florida. In Tallahassee, the mercury dipped to a record low 
of 34 degrees. Melbourne had a record low of 49, and Miami tied a record with 
59. Temperatures dipped below freezing in the Great Lakes and the northern Ohio 
Valley. Ft. Wayne, Ind., reported a record low of 27. Temperatures were in the 
40s in northern New England, where the fall foliage season is just past its 
peak. 
</P>
