<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE; 
</P>
<P>
SCHULLER SELLS MAUI PROPERTY TO SIMON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rev. Robert H. Schuller announced that his ministry's multimillion-dollar 
Maui property has been sold as a "family retreat" to former U.S. Treasury 
Secretary William E. Simon. Schuller, who did not reveal the price tag for the 
43-acre retreat, told his congregation in Garden Grove's Crystal Cathedral that 
the transaction "has poured multiplied millions of dollars into a $23-million 
Family Life Center." Schuller had been seeking a buyer for the prime acreage 
for more than a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
