<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAPE SUSPECT SURRENDERS TO SWAT TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man suspected of raping and kidnaping a 19-year old woman was arrested Sunday 
after police surrounded a house in South San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect, Jose Luis Estrada, 32, surrendered after a SWAT team was summoned, 
ending a 3 1/2-hour standoff in the 2200 block of Conifer Avenue, according to 
San Diego police spokesman Bill Robinson. 
</P>
<P>
The incident ended peacefully when Estrada surrendered at 4:45 p.m. to a 
bilingual police detective, Carlos Chacon. Officers were attempting to 
determine if Chacon was armed during the confrontation. 
</P>
<P>
Estrada is suspected of the rape and kidnaping of a 19-year-old woman that 
occurred on Saturday evening in the same area where Estrada was apprehended, 
Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim told police she was able to escape after being repeatedly raped and 
beaten. She was treated at Chula Vista Community Hospital, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
Estrada was being questioned by police Sunday evening, Robinson said. 
</P>
