<P>
RAIN MAY CONTINUE THROUGH TUESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After a mostly cloudy and sometimes drizzly weekend it finally feels like fall 
in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
The rain that fell over the weekend may continue through Tuesday, when San 
Diego weather forecasters have predicted mostly cloudy skies and a slight 
chance of light rain, according to National Weather Service forecaster Wally 
Cegiel. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego County rainfall totals varied from a trace in some areas to .09 of an 
inch in Chula Vista to 1.2 inches on Palomar Mountain during the 24-hour period 
that ended Sunday at 4 p.m., according to the National Weather Service. 
</P>
<P>
The temperature forecast for all San Diego areas today is partly cloudy with 
highs ranging from 67 to 74 and lows in the upper 50s. 
</P>
