<HEADLINE>
<P>
CYCLING TOUR OF PALM SPRINGS; 
</P>
<P>
ORAVETZ TAKES FINAL STAGE, BUT VONDERHE WINS EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB HOWELLS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Greg Oravetz of the Coors Light bicycle team won a photo-finish sprint in the 
final stage of the Tour of Palm Springs Sunday, and Jay Vonderhe of Team 
Montgomery was the overall winner of the three-stage race. 
</P>
<P>
Oravetz, 22, of Boulder, Colo., led a 15-rider break that pulled away from the 
main pack with 20 laps left in the 66-lap, 40-mile criterium in downtown Palm 
Springs. 
</P>
<P>
Oravetz then held on to edge Mike Costello of Ft. Collins, Colo., by two 
inches. They finished in 1 hour 25 minutes 39 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Oravetz finished third in the tour, behind Vonderhe and Scott Moninger of 
Boulder. 
</P>
<P>
Katrin Tobin of Ketchum, Ida., won the women's criterium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
