<TEXT>
<P>
Fat Lever scored 12 points in the fourth quarter and the Denver Nuggets broke 
open the game in the final three minutes for a 135-129 victory over 
Jugoplastika Split of Yugoslavia in the championship game of the McDonald's 
Open basketball tournament at Rome. 
</P>
<P>
It was the third straight year an NBA team has won. The Milwaukee Bucks won the 
inaugural event in 1987 and the Boston Celtics won last year. 
</P>
<P>
Lever and Davis each finished with 26 points. Center Danny Schayes led the 
Nuggets with 29. 
</P>
<P>
Bob McAdoo scored 36 points to lead Philips Milan to a 136-104 victory over 
Barcelona in the consolation game. 
