<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Longshot Caltech turned back a rally in the stretch by favored Yankee Affair to 
win the $750,000 Budweiser International at Laurel Race Course in Maryland. 
</P>
<P>
Ridden by Rene Douglas, Caltech led almost the entire way. 
</P>
<P>
Yankee Affair, the 8-5 favorite ridden by Jose Santos, finished second, 1 3/4 
lengths back and 2 1/2 in front of another longshot, Mister Wonderful, ridden 
by Fernando Toro. 
</P>
<P>
Caltech added the $450,000 winner's share to the $157,970 he earned in 15 
previous career starts. He returned $28.80, $9 and $7.80. Yankee Affair, a 
7-year-old who has won more than $1 million this year, got $150,000. He paid 
$3.20 and $2.60. 
