<P>
Quake Doesn't Shake Muni Bonds: California's municipal bond market, the 
nation's largest, felt barely a ripple from the Bay Area earthquake, though 
some of the roads, bridges and buildings financed by the bonds sustained 
damage. Prices of the bonds were virtually unaffected by the quake. Mutual fund 
operators said they received few panicky calls from investors in 
California-based municipal bond funds, and almost none of the investors pulled 
out. 
