Photo, COLOR, Part of the quake-damaged section of the Bay Bridge's upper deck 
is lowered to barge for repairs. United Press International; Photo, (Southland 
Edition) Amid the RubbleFor some San Francisco residents, things began to feel 
normal again. There were even those who enjoyed Sunday afternoon walks in the 
park. But in much of the Bay Area, the earthquake of five days before still 
intruded on most aspects of life. For residents of the Marina district, who 
police carefully escorted through the area, there was little to salvage, above. 
Many of the quake-damaged buildings in that part of the city face demolition. ; 
Photo, Buck Helm Associated Press 
</P>
