SCHOOLS: Anaheim City School District parents are expected to endorse 
year-round schools for their overcrowded district, where enrollments increased 
5% this year. . . . Supt. Meliton Lopez hopes that results of a recent survey 
will show that parents support the change. . . . He noted a recent Times Orange 
County poll showing that 58% of county residents favor year-round schools. . . 
. Anaheim would be the county's fifth district with year-round scheduling, 
which would begin in July, 1990. Lanie Jones and Rick VanderKyff 
