<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
STORE OWNER BEATEN, IN CRITICAL CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Anaheim liquor store owner was severely beaten Sunday night by a man trying 
to rob the store, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, whose name was withheld until relatives could be notified, was 
rushed to UCI Medical Center in Orange, where he was in critical condition with 
unspecified injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Police Sgt. Fred Roush said the robber entered the liquor store in the 2600 
block of West Lincoln Avenue at 8:26 p.m. and demanded cash. The men struggled, 
and the robber eventually fled. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the attacker was described as white, 18 to 19 years old, 5 feet, 6 
inches tall and 190 pounds, with shoulder-length, brownish-blond hair, blue 
jeans and a white T-shirt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
