<P>
CRASH KILLS COUPLE IN DESERT HOT SPRINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Irvine man and his wife were killed Sunday afternoon in a three-vehicle 
accident in Desert Hot Springs, the Riverside County coroner's office reported. 
</P>
<P>
The couple, identified as Lawrence Beck Jr., 44, and his wife Blanca Beck, 48, 
died in the 2:50 p.m. accident on Palm Drive just north of 20th Avenue, said 
Daniel Holstein, a deputy county coroner in Indio. A third person was killed in 
one of the other cars, but his identity had not been determined late Sunday, 
Holstein said. 
