<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; 
</P>
<P>
2 ROB RESTAURANT, SHOOT AT MALL GUARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two robbers, one brandishing an automatic handgun, held up a restaurant in the 
MainPlace shopping mall and then shot at a security guard who tried to stop 
them, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The two robbed Boardwalk Fries in the mall, on the 2800 block of North Main 
Street, about 8:30 p.m. Saturday, said Police Sgt. John Dittus. Mall security 
guard Darren Cole chased the two men into the parking lot, where one of them 
turned and fired at Cole several times and missed, Dittus said. 
</P>
<P>
Another guard, James Smith, spotted the robbers getting away in a small black 
pickup truck and chased them to Culver Avenue and Main Street in Orange, where 
they abandoned the truck and fled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
