<HEADLINE>
<P>
SWISS JOBLESS RATE 0.5% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BERN, Switzerland 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The number of unemployed in Switzerland declined another 2.6% in September to a 
total of 15,222 people, the Federal Industry and Labor Bureau reported today. 
</P>
<P>
The overall jobless rate remained stable at 0.5%, it said. 
</P>
<P>
Available jobs registered with employment offices also rose, however, 
increasing 2.3% to 17,677. 
</P>
</TEXT>
